main event: Two unidentified objects were observed in the sky maneuvering slowly over Corpus Christi, Texas on July 21, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were observed for approximately 45 minutes, with erratic maneuvers noted for 15 - 20 minutes., The objects were described as round, white or gray, and appeared metallic., No physical evidence such as photographs or radar returns was available for the objects., The conclusion drawn from the report classified the objects as balloons., The weather conditions were clear, with premium visibility, allowing the observer to see the objects distinctly.
sighted object: two round white or gray objects
witness description: The witness expressed a keen interest in the subject and previously had confusion regarding the existence of such objects, but now believes they may be real and possibly from outer space.
